{"title_page": "Fregeneda\u2013Almendra pegmatitic field", "text_new": "The '''Fregeneda\u2013Almendra pegmatitic field''' is a geologic area in the [[Iberian Peninsula]] extending across the Portuguese district of [[Guarda District|Guarda]] and the Spanish province of [[Province of Salamanca|Salamanca]]. Part of the {{ill|Central Iberian Zone|es|Zona Centroib\u00e9rica}},{{Sfn|Roda-Robles|Vieira|Pesquera|Lima|2010|p=33}} it is located in the western part of a narrow E\u2013W metamorphic belt.{{Sfn|Roda|Vieira|Lima|Pesquera|2007}} Comprising a variety of [[Granite|granitic]] [[pegmatite]]s, where some rocks are rich in [[lithium]]. The Li minerals include [[spodumene]], [[petalite]], lithian muscovite and [[montebrasite]].{{sfn|Roda-Robles|Pesquera|Gil-Crespo|Vieira|2016|p=106}}\n\nA mining site for the extraction of lithium, [[tin]], [[niobium]] and [[tantalium]] is located in [[La Fregeneda]] area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://info.igme.es/ielig/LIGInfo.aspx?codigo=CI078|publisher=[[Geological and Mining Institute of Spain|IGME]]|title=Yacimientos de Sn y Li de La Fregeneda (Mina Feli o de Alabancos)}}</ref>\n\n== Bibliography ==\n;References\n{{reflist}}\n;Bibliography\n* {{Cite journal|last=Roda Robles|first=E.|last2=Pesquera P\u00e9rez|first2=A.|last3=Velasco Rold\u00e1n|first3=F|last4=Font\u00e1n|first4=F|year=1999|title=The granitic pegmatites of the Fregeneda area (Salamanca, Spain): characteristics and petrogenesis|journal=Mineralogical Magazine|volume=63|issue=4|pages=535\u2013558|doi=10.1180/002646199548709}}\n* {{Cite journal|url=https://www.fc.up.pt/peg2007/files/roda.pdf|title=The Fregeneda \u2013 Almendra pegmatitic field (Spain & Portugal): mineral assemblages and regional zonation|first=E.|last=Roda|first2=R.|ref=harv|last2=Vieira|first3=R|last3=Lima|first4=A|last4=Pesquera|first5=F|last5=Noronha|first6=F|last6=Font\u00e1n|journal=Granitic Pegmatites: The State of the Art \u2013 International Symposium. 06th \u2013 12th May 2007, Porto, Portugal|year=2